    "recap_headline": "Oregon State University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "PORTLAND, Ore.\n\u2013 Four Oregon State pitchers combined for 11 strikeouts and\nBryce Hubbard\ncollected a pair of hits in the Beavers' 3-1 loss to Portland Tuesday night at Joe Etzel Field.\nThe Beavers loaded the bases with two down in the ninth inning. Hubbard doubled to open the inning, then watched as pinch hitters\nEthan Porter\nand\nBryson Glassco\ndrew walks. But Portland's Kaden Segel got\nJacob Galloway\nto fly out to left to end the game.\nConnor Mendez\n,\nWyatt Queen\n,\nMason Pike\nand\nTanner Douglas\ncombined to hold the Pilots (11-7 overall) to six hits and four walks while striking out 11.\nMendez started and allowed four hits and two runs in 3 1/3 innings. He took the loss to drop to 0-1.\nTanner Douglas\n, in a return to Portland, struck out four in 2 2/3 scoreless innings.\nThe Beavers (14-5) scored their lone run in the third when\nNyan Hayes\ncame in from third on a bases-loaded wild pitch to\nEaston Talt\n.\nThe Pilots equaled the score on a sacrifice fly in the bottom half of the third. UP went ahead with a single run in the fourth and gave itself an insurance run in the sixth.\nOregon State continues its eight-game road trip with three at UC Irvine. The series opens Friday night at 6 p.m. PT. The game will air live on the Beaver Sports Network and ESPN+.\nFollow Us On Social\nFor more information on the Oregon State baseball team, follow the club's official X account at X.com/BeaverBaseball, by Facebook at Facebook.com/OregonStateBaseball, at BeaverBaseball.OSUBeavers.com on BlueSky or on Instagram at Instagram.com/BeaverBaseball.\nOUR MISSION\nOregon State Athletics strives to Build Excellent Authentic Visionary Student-Athletes (Go BEAVS)."
  },
